{"title_page": "Nimrat Khaira", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{short description|Indian singer and actress}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Nimrat Khaira\n| image            = Nimratpal Khaira.jpg\n| caption          = Nimrat Khaira\n| background       = solo_singer\n| birth_name       = Nimratpal Kaur Khaira\n| birth_date       = <!-- This information has been repeatedly challenged in the past, so we err on the side of caution: Instagram posts, unless they explicitly say \"I was born on (date)\", are not suitable as a source for this parameter. Type \"WP:BLPPRIVACY\", \"WP:BLPPRIMARY\" and \"WP:PSTS\" into the search box for more information. -->\n| birth_place      = [[Batala]], [[Punjab, India]]\n| genre            = Punjabi Folk\n| occupation       = {{flatlist|\n*Singer\n*actress}}\n| instrument       = Vocals\n| years_active     = 2014\u2013present\n| associated_acts  = {{flatlist|\n* [[Amrinder Gill]]\n* [[Tarsem Jassar]]}}\n| label            = {{flatlist|\n*Brown Studios\n*[[Rhythm Boyz]]\n*Panj-aab Records\n*[[White Hill Studio|White Hill Music]]}}\n| website          = {{Facebook|NimratKhairaOfficial|Nimrat Khaira}}\n}}\n'''Nimrat Khaira''' is an [[India]]n singer, actress and playback singer known for her work in [[Punjabi language|Punjabi]]-language music and films. She has been nominated for two [[Filmfare Punjabi Awards]] and one [[PTC Punjabi Film Awards|PTC Punjabi Film award]]. She is scheduled to marry Anmol Gill on 14 February, 2023.\n\n==Career==\nShe is the winner of [[Voice of Punjab]] season 3.<ref>{{cite web|title=Voice of Punjab Season 3 winners|url=http://www.yespunjab.com/entertainment/item/6762-nimrat-pal-kaur-and-anant-pal-singh-win-\u2018voice-of-punjab\u2019-titles}}</ref> She gained fame after the release of her single \"Ishq Kacheri\".<ref>{{cite news|title= Nimrat Khaira female singers |url= http://www.tribuneindia.com/news/life-style/her-wakhra-swag/317350.html |accessdate=2 November 2016}}</ref> She performed at Saras Mela, held in [[Bathinda]].<ref>{{cite news|title= Saras Mela Performance |url= http://www.tribuneindia.com/news/bathinda/a-blend-of-culture-tradition-and-artwork-on-display/309618.html |accessdate=2 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= Saras Mela Performance |url= http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chandigarh/Regional-Saras-Mela-at-Bathinda-from-Oct-14-rural-development-minister-Maluka-to-inaugurate/articleshow/54818925.cms |accessdate=2 November 2016}}</ref> She hosted the third edition of Radio Mirchi Music Awards with [[Amrit Maan]].<ref>{{cite news|title= Radio Mirchi Music Awards |url= http://www.aninews.in/newsdetail-NQ/MjkyOTcx/radio-mirchi-honours-best-of-punjabi-music-at-mma-punjabi.html |accessdate= 22 March 2017}}</ref>\n\nShe started her singing career from song \"Rab Karke\" which was released on 24 September 2015 and was duo associated with Nishawn Bhullar and was released on record label Punj-aab Records. The song received good response from audience but she got much fame through her next two songs \"Ishq Kacheri\" and \"SP De Rank Wargi\" both released in 2016. She continued her success with songs like \"Salute Wajde\" in 2016. In 2017, she launched many singles many of them overcame as massive hits like \"Rohab Rakhdi\", \"Dubai Wale Sheikh\", \"Suit\" and \"Designer\". She also won Best female vocalist award for her duo \"Dubai Wale Sheikh\" from [[Manje Bistre]] at Brit Asia Awards and nominated at Filmare Punjabi Award. Also her song \"Designer\" composed by Deep Jandu came in controversy after a foreign composer \"Zwirek\" claimed the music and the song was removed from YouTube but later, the song was readded to YouTube after music was proved legally original.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dailypost.in/news/entertainment/nimrat-khairas-designer-song-deleted-youtube/|title=Nimrat Khaira's 'Designer' song deleted from Youtube|date=16 December 2017|work=Latest Punjab News, Breaking News Punjab, India News {{!}} Daily Post|access-date=11 October 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Songs==\n{| class=wikitable\n|-\n! Year\n! Song\n! Associated With\n|-\n|2015\n| Rab Karke\n| Nishawn Bhullar\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|2016\n|SP De Rank Wargi\n|Desi Crew\n|-\n| Ishq Kacheri\n| Preet Hundal\n|-\n|Salute Wajde \n|ArZzz\n|-\n| Taanvi Changa Lagda\n| ArZzz\n|-\n|rowspan=\"7\"|2017\n|Rohab Rakhdi\n|ArZzz \n|-\n|Jhumke\n|Movie \u2013 Sargi with [[Jassi Gill]] and [[Babbal Rai]]\n|-\n|Dubai Wale Sheikh<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://m.filmfare.com/news/bollywood/nominations-for-the-jio-filmfare-awards-punjabi-2018_-27178.html|title=Nominations for the Jio Filmfare Awards (Punjabi) 2018|work=filmfare.com|access-date=19 May 2018}}</ref>\n| [[Gippy Grewal]] in Movie [[Manje Bistre]]\n|-\n|Akhar (female version)\n| [[Amrinder Gill]] in [[Lahoriye]]\n|-\n|Bhangra Gidha<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://chandigarhmetro.com/bhangra-gidha-song-nimrat-khaira-new-punjabi-official-video/|title=Bhangra Gidha by Nimrat Khaira (New Punjabi Song) {{!}} Official Video|date=30 June 2017|work=Chandigarh Metro|access-date=19 May 2018}}</ref>\n|Babbu\n|-\n|Suit<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://chandigarhmetro.com/suit-nimrat-khaira-mankirt-aulakh-latest-punjabi-song/|title=Suit by Nimrat Khaira Ft. Mankirt Aulakh (Latest Punjabi Song) {{!}} Official Video|date=10 October 2017|work=Chandigarh Metro|access-date=19 May 2018}}</ref>\n|Mankirt Aulakh\n|-\n|Designer<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://chandigarhmetro.com/designer-nimrat-khaira-new-punjabi-song-2017-official-video/|title=Designer by (Nimrat Khaira) \u2013 New Punjabi Song {{!}} Official Video Out|date=21 November 2017|work=Chandigarh Metro|access-date=19 May 2018}}</ref>\n|Humble Music\n|-\n|rowspan=\"6\"|2018\n| Brobar Boli<ref>{{cite news\n | title = Brobar Boli, New Year 2018 Gifted Song \n | url = http://redmux.com/song/brobar-boli/\n | access-date = 30 December 2017\n | publisher=RedMux\n | archive-date = 7 January 2018 }}</ref>\n|[[Desi Routz]], White hill\n|-\n| Ranihaar<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://punjabipollywood.com/ranihaar-new-punjabi-song-by-nimrat-khaira-official-video-and-lyrics/|title=Ranihaar (New Punjabi Song) by Nimrat Khaira {{!}} Official Video and Lyrics|date=23 July 2018|work=PunjabiPollywood.com \u2013 Gossip, Movies, Songs, Photos, Videos|access-date=23 July 2018}}</ref>\n| White Hill Music\n|-\n| Sun Sohniye\n| with [[Ranjit Bawa]] from [[Afsar (2018 film)|Afsar]]\n|-\n| Udhaar Chalda\n| with [[Gurnam Bhullar]] from Afsar\n|-\n| Khat\n| from Afsar\n|-\n| Sacha Jhootha<ref>{{Citation|title=Sacha Jhootha - Single by Nimrat Khaira|url=https://music.apple.com/nz/album/sacha-jhootha-single/1445676447|language=en-au|website=[[Apple Music]]|access-date=2020-02-29}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"2\"|Brown Studio\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|2019\n| Tohar\n|-\n| Jattan De Munde\n| with [[Tarsem Jassar]] from [[Rabb Da Radio 2]]\n|-\n| Channan\n|Tarsem Jassar from Rabb Da Radio\n|-\n| Baddlan De Kaalje\n| With [[Amrinder Gill]] in film [[Chal Mera Putt]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|2020\n| Lehnga\n| \n|-\n| Majhe Vall Da\n| featured in song by [[Amrinder Gill]] from ''[[Chal Mera Putt 2]]''\n|}\n\n==Film career==\nShe started her film career in 2017 with ''[[Lahoriye]]'', wherein she played the role of Kikkar([[Amrinder Gill]])'s sister ''Harleen Kaur''. Her performance in film was appreciated by audience. She was also nominated for ''Best Debut Performance'' and ''Best Supporting Actress'' in different Award Ceremonies.<ref>{{cite web|title=Nimrat Khaira Films|url=https://m.imdb.com/name/nm8674718/}}</ref>\n\nHer second film ''[[Afsar (2018 film)|Afsar]]'' is set to be released on 5 October 2018. Film marks as Debut as lead actress for ''Nimrat Khaira''. In film, ''Nimrat Khaira'' had shared screen with [[Tarsem Jassar]]. She had played the role of Harman who is Teacher in Government school.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/punjabi/movies/news/afsar-first-look-pollywood-gets-a-new-on-screen-jodi-nimrat-khaira-and-tasrem-jassar/articleshow/64540403.cms|title=\u2018Afsar\u2019 first look: Pollywood gets a new on-screen jodi \u2013 Nimrat Khaira and Tasrem Jassar |work=The Times of India|access-date=23 July 2018}}</ref> In 2020, her ''[[Jodi (2020 film)|Jodi]]'' is releasing, which is written and directed by [[Amberdeep Singh]]. In the film, she is co-starring [[Diljit Dosanjh]]. It is her second collaboration with Singh and [[Rhythm Boyz Entertainment]] after ''[[Lahoriye]]'' (2017).\n\n==Filmography==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Key\n| style=\"background:#FFFFCC;\"| {{dagger|alt=Films that have not yet been released}}\n| Denotes films that have not yet been released\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Film\n! Role\n! Notes\n! Language \n|-\n| 2017|| ''[[Lahoriye]]'' || Harleen Kaur || Punjabi Film Debut || Punjabi\n|-\n|2018||''[[Afsar (2018 film)|Afsar]] || Harman || with [[Tarsem Jassar]]\n| Punjabi\n|-\n| 2020 || style=\"background:#FFFFCC;\"|''[[Jodi (2020 film)|Jodi]]''{{dagger|alt=Films that have not yet been released}} || {{TBA}} ||  || Punjabi\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! width=5%|Year\n! style=\"width:20%;\"|Film\n! style=\"width:30%;\"|Award Ceremony\n! style=\"width:29%;\"|Category\n! style=\"width:15%;\"|Result\n|-\n|rowspan=\"6\"|2018\n|rowspan=\"2\"|''[[Lahoriye]]''\n|rowspan=\"3\"|Brit Asia Awards<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://britasia.tv/full-list-of-winners-from-the-punjabi-film-awards-2018/|title=FULL LIST OF WINNERS FROM THE PUNJABI FILM AWARDS 2018 \u2013 BritAsia TV|date=14 May 2018|publisher=BritAsia TV|access-date=14 August 2018}}</ref>\n|Best Debut Performance\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Supporting Actress\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|''[[Manje Bistre]]''\n| Best Female Vocalist\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Filmfare Awards Punjabi]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.filmfare.com/awards/filmfare-awards-punjabi-2018/nominations|title=Filmfare Awards Punjabi 2018 Nominations {{!}} Filmfare.com|website=filmfare.com|access-date=14 August 2018}}</ref>\n| Best playback singer(female)\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|''Lahoriye''\n|rowspan=\"2\"| Best Debut Female\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[PTC Punjabi Film Awards]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ptcpunjabifilmawards.in/nomination/|title=NOMINATION \u2013 PTC Punjabi Film Awards 2018 {{!}} PTC Punjabi|website=ptcpunjabifilmawards.in|access-date=14 August 2018}}</ref>\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\"|2019\n| ''[[Afsar (2018 film)|Afsar]]''\n| Brit Asia TV Awards\n| Best Female Playback Vocalist\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|8674718}}\n* {{Facebook|NimratKhairaOfficial}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:khaira, Nimrat}}\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Punjabi-language singers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{short description|Indian singer and actress}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Nimrat Khaira\n| image            = Nimratpal Khaira.jpg\n| caption          = Nimrat Khaira\n| background       = solo_singer\n| birth_name       = Nimratpal Kaur Khaira\n| birth_date       = <!-- This information has been repeatedly challenged in the past, so we err on the side of caution: Instagram posts, unless they explicitly say \"I was born on (date)\", are not suitable as a source for this parameter. Type \"WP:BLPPRIVACY\", \"WP:BLPPRIMARY\" and \"WP:PSTS\" into the search box for more information. -->\n| birth_place      = [[Batala]], [[Punjab, India]]\n| genre            = Punjabi Folk\n| occupation       = {{flatlist|\n*Singer\n*actress}}\n| instrument       = Vocals\n| years_active     = 2014\u2013present\n| associated_acts  = {{flatlist|\n* [[Amrinder Gill]]\n* [[Tarsem Jassar]]}}\n| label            = {{flatlist|\n*Brown Studios\n*[[Rhythm Boyz]]\n*Panj-aab Records\n*[[White Hill Studio|White Hill Music]]}}\n| website          = {{Facebook|NimratKhairaOfficial|Nimrat Khaira}}\n}}\n'''Nimrat Khaira''' is an [[India]]n singer, actress and playback singer known for her work in [[Punjabi language|Punjabi]]-language music and films. She has been nominated for two [[Filmfare Punjabi Awards]] and one [[PTC Punjabi Film Awards|PTC Punjabi Film award]].\n\n==Career==\nShe is the winner of [[Voice of Punjab]] season 3.<ref>{{cite web|title=Voice of Punjab Season 3 winners|url=http://www.yespunjab.com/entertainment/item/6762-nimrat-pal-kaur-and-anant-pal-singh-win-\u2018voice-of-punjab\u2019-titles}}</ref> She gained fame after the release of her single \"Ishq Kacheri\".<ref>{{cite news|title= Nimrat Khaira female singers |url= http://www.tribuneindia.com/news/life-style/her-wakhra-swag/317350.html |accessdate=2 November 2016}}</ref> She performed at Saras Mela, held in [[Bathinda]].<ref>{{cite news|title= Saras Mela Performance |url= http://www.tribuneindia.com/news/bathinda/a-blend-of-culture-tradition-and-artwork-on-display/309618.html |accessdate=2 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title= Saras Mela Performance |url= http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chandigarh/Regional-Saras-Mela-at-Bathinda-from-Oct-14-rural-development-minister-Maluka-to-inaugurate/articleshow/54818925.cms |accessdate=2 November 2016}}</ref> She hosted the third edition of Radio Mirchi Music Awards with [[Amrit Maan]].<ref>{{cite news|title= Radio Mirchi Music Awards |url= http://www.aninews.in/newsdetail-NQ/MjkyOTcx/radio-mirchi-honours-best-of-punjabi-music-at-mma-punjabi.html |accessdate= 22 March 2017}}</ref>\n\nShe started her singing career from song \"Rab Karke\" which was released on 24 September 2015 and was duo associated with Nishawn Bhullar and was released on record label Punj-aab Records. The song received good response from audience but she got much fame through her next two songs \"Ishq Kacheri\" and \"SP De Rank Wargi\" both released in 2016. She continued her success with songs like \"Salute Wajde\" in 2016. In 2017, she launched many singles many of them overcame as massive hits like \"Rohab Rakhdi\", \"Dubai Wale Sheikh\", \"Suit\" and \"Designer\". She also won Best female vocalist award for her duo \"Dubai Wale Sheikh\" from [[Manje Bistre]] at Brit Asia Awards and nominated at Filmare Punjabi Award. Also her song \"Designer\" composed by Deep Jandu came in controversy after a foreign composer \"Zwirek\" claimed the music and the song was removed from YouTube but later, the song was readded to YouTube after music was proved legally original.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://dailypost.in/news/entertainment/nimrat-khairas-designer-song-deleted-youtube/|title=Nimrat Khaira's 'Designer' song deleted from Youtube|date=16 December 2017|work=Latest Punjab News, Breaking News Punjab, India News {{!}} Daily Post|access-date=11 October 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Songs==\n{| class=wikitable\n|-\n! Year\n! Song\n! Associated With\n|-\n|2015\n| Rab Karke\n| Nishawn Bhullar\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|2016\n|SP De Rank Wargi\n|Desi Crew\n|-\n| Ishq Kacheri\n| Preet Hundal\n|-\n|Salute Wajde \n|ArZzz\n|-\n| Taanvi Changa Lagda\n| ArZzz\n|-\n|rowspan=\"7\"|2017\n|Rohab Rakhdi\n|ArZzz \n|-\n|Jhumke\n|Movie \u2013 Sargi with [[Jassi Gill]] and [[Babbal Rai]]\n|-\n|Dubai Wale Sheikh<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://m.filmfare.com/news/bollywood/nominations-for-the-jio-filmfare-awards-punjabi-2018_-27178.html|title=Nominations for the Jio Filmfare Awards (Punjabi) 2018|work=filmfare.com|access-date=19 May 2018}}</ref>\n| [[Gippy Grewal]] in Movie [[Manje Bistre]]\n|-\n|Akhar (female version)\n| [[Amrinder Gill]] in [[Lahoriye]]\n|-\n|Bhangra Gidha<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://chandigarhmetro.com/bhangra-gidha-song-nimrat-khaira-new-punjabi-official-video/|title=Bhangra Gidha by Nimrat Khaira (New Punjabi Song) {{!}} Official Video|date=30 June 2017|work=Chandigarh Metro|access-date=19 May 2018}}</ref>\n|Babbu\n|-\n|Suit<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://chandigarhmetro.com/suit-nimrat-khaira-mankirt-aulakh-latest-punjabi-song/|title=Suit by Nimrat Khaira Ft. Mankirt Aulakh (Latest Punjabi Song) {{!}} Official Video|date=10 October 2017|work=Chandigarh Metro|access-date=19 May 2018}}</ref>\n|Mankirt Aulakh\n|-\n|Designer<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://chandigarhmetro.com/designer-nimrat-khaira-new-punjabi-song-2017-official-video/|title=Designer by (Nimrat Khaira) \u2013 New Punjabi Song {{!}} Official Video Out|date=21 November 2017|work=Chandigarh Metro|access-date=19 May 2018}}</ref>\n|Humble Music\n|-\n|rowspan=\"6\"|2018\n| Brobar Boli<ref>{{cite news\n | title = Brobar Boli, New Year 2018 Gifted Song \n | url = http://redmux.com/song/brobar-boli/\n | access-date = 30 December 2017\n | publisher=RedMux\n | archive-date = 7 January 2018 }}</ref>\n|[[Desi Routz]], White hill\n|-\n| Ranihaar<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://punjabipollywood.com/ranihaar-new-punjabi-song-by-nimrat-khaira-official-video-and-lyrics/|title=Ranihaar (New Punjabi Song) by Nimrat Khaira {{!}} Official Video and Lyrics|date=23 July 2018|work=PunjabiPollywood.com \u2013 Gossip, Movies, Songs, Photos, Videos|access-date=23 July 2018}}</ref>\n| White Hill Music\n|-\n| Sun Sohniye\n| with [[Ranjit Bawa]] from [[Afsar (2018 film)|Afsar]]\n|-\n| Udhaar Chalda\n| with [[Gurnam Bhullar]] from Afsar\n|-\n| Khat\n| from Afsar\n|-\n| Sacha Jhootha<ref>{{Citation|title=Sacha Jhootha - Single by Nimrat Khaira|url=https://music.apple.com/nz/album/sacha-jhootha-single/1445676447|language=en-au|website=[[Apple Music]]|access-date=2020-02-29}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"2\"|Brown Studio\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|2019\n| Tohar\n|-\n| Jattan De Munde\n| with [[Tarsem Jassar]] from [[Rabb Da Radio 2]]\n|-\n| Channan\n|Tarsem Jassar from Rabb Da Radio\n|-\n| Baddlan De Kaalje\n| With [[Amrinder Gill]] in film [[Chal Mera Putt]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|2020\n| Lehnga\n| \n|-\n| Majhe Vall Da\n| featured in song by [[Amrinder Gill]] from ''[[Chal Mera Putt 2]]''\n|}\n\n==Film career==\nShe started her film career in 2017 with ''[[Lahoriye]]'', wherein she played the role of Kikkar([[Amrinder Gill]])'s sister ''Harleen Kaur''. Her performance in film was appreciated by audience. She was also nominated for ''Best Debut Performance'' and ''Best Supporting Actress'' in different Award Ceremonies.<ref>{{cite web|title=Nimrat Khaira Films|url=https://m.imdb.com/name/nm8674718/}}</ref>\n\nHer second film ''[[Afsar (2018 film)|Afsar]]'' is set to be released on 5 October 2018. Film marks as Debut as lead actress for ''Nimrat Khaira''. In film, ''Nimrat Khaira'' had shared screen with [[Tarsem Jassar]]. She had played the role of Harman who is Teacher in Government school.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/punjabi/movies/news/afsar-first-look-pollywood-gets-a-new-on-screen-jodi-nimrat-khaira-and-tasrem-jassar/articleshow/64540403.cms|title=\u2018Afsar\u2019 first look: Pollywood gets a new on-screen jodi \u2013 Nimrat Khaira and Tasrem Jassar |work=The Times of India|access-date=23 July 2018}}</ref> In 2020, her ''[[Jodi (2020 film)|Jodi]]'' is releasing, which is written and directed by [[Amberdeep Singh]]. In the film, she is co-starring [[Diljit Dosanjh]]. It is her second collaboration with Singh and [[Rhythm Boyz Entertainment]] after ''[[Lahoriye]]'' (2017).\n\n==Filmography==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Key\n| style=\"background:#FFFFCC;\"| {{dagger|alt=Films that have not yet been released}}\n| Denotes films that have not yet been released\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Film\n! Role\n! Notes\n! Language \n|-\n| 2017|| ''[[Lahoriye]]'' || Harleen Kaur || Punjabi Film Debut || Punjabi\n|-\n|2018||''[[Afsar (2018 film)|Afsar]] || Harman || with [[Tarsem Jassar]]\n| Punjabi\n|-\n| 2020 || style=\"background:#FFFFCC;\"|''[[Jodi (2020 film)|Jodi]]''{{dagger|alt=Films that have not yet been released}} || {{TBA}} ||  || Punjabi\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! width=5%|Year\n! style=\"width:20%;\"|Film\n! style=\"width:30%;\"|Award Ceremony\n! style=\"width:29%;\"|Category\n! style=\"width:15%;