5|C|disp=table}}||\n*Magherally, County Down (1 Jan 1979)\n|-\n!February\n|{{convert|17.8|C|disp=table}} ||\n*Bryansford, County Down (13 Feb 1998)<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n|{{convert|-15.0|C|disp=table}}||\n*Armagh, County Armagh (7 Feb 1895)\n|-\n!March\n|{{convert|21.8|C|disp=table}} ||\n*Armagh, County Armagh (29 Mar 1965)\n|{{convert|-14.8|C|disp=table}}||\n*Katesbridge, County Down (2 Mar 2001)\n|-\n!April\n|{{convert|24.5|C|disp=table}} ||\n*Boom Hall, County Londonderry (26 Apr 1984)\n|{{convert|-8.5|C|disp=table}} ||\n*Killylane, County Antrim (10 Apr 1998)\n|-\n!May\n|{{convert|28.0|C|disp=table}} ||\n*Knockarevan, County Fermanagh (31 May 1947)\n|{{convert|-6.5|C|disp=table}} ||\n*Moydamlaght, County Londonderry (7 May 1982)\n|-\n!June\n|{{convert|30.8|C|disp=table}} ||\n*Knockarevan, County Fermanagh (30 Jun 1976)\n|{{convert|-2.4|C|disp=table}} ||\n*Lough Navar Forest, County Fermanagh (4 Jun 1991)\n|-\n!July\n|{{convert|30.8|C|disp=table}} ||\n*Shaw's Bridge, Belfast, County Antrim (12 Jul 1983)\n|{{convert|-1.1|C|disp=table}} ||\n*Lislap Forest, County Tyrone (17 Jul 1971)\n|-\n!August\n|{{convert|30.6|C|disp=table}} ||\n*Tandragee Ballylisk, County Armagh (2 Aug 1995)\n|{{convert|-1.9|C|disp=table}} ||\n*Katesbridge, County Down (24 Aug 2014)\n|-\n!September\n|{{convert|27.6|C|disp=table}} ||\n*Armagh, County Armagh (1 Sep 1906)\n|{{convert|-3.6|C|disp=table}} ||\n*Katesbridge, County Down (29 Sep 2018)\n|-\n!October\n|{{convert|24.1|C|disp=table}} ||\n*Strabane, County Tyrone (10 Oct 1969)\n|{{convert|-7.2|C|disp=table}} ||\n*Lough Navar Forest, County Fermanagh (18 Oct 1993)\n|-\n!November\n|{{convert|18.5|C|disp=table}} ||\n*Murlough, County Down (3 Nov 1979)\n*Murlough, County Down (1 Nov 2007)\n*Murlough, County Down (10 Nov 2015)\n|{{convert|-12.2|C|disp=table}} ||\n*Lisburn, County Antrim (15 Nov 1919)\n|-\n!December\n|{{convert|16.7|C|disp=table}} ||\n*Ballykelly, County Londonderry (2 Dec 1948)\n|{{convert|-18.7|C|disp=table}} ||\n*Castlederg, County Tyrone (24 Dec 2010)\n|}\n\n==Scotland==\n{{main|Climate of Scotland}}\n\n[[Scotland]] is generally cool compared to the rest of the UK, and the climate at altitude merges into ''Cfc'', ''Dfc'', or ''ET'' on the K\u00f6ppen system, with average minimum temperatures in January of {{convert|-0.2|C|F|1}}. The Central Lowlands have higher temperatures during the summer than any other part of Scotland, and have also broken some records for the whole of the UK. [[Aviemore]] is considered one of the coldest inhabited places, with its inland location and an altitude of about 210 metres. The wettest month in Scotland is January; most months are wetter than other parts of the UK, except for the late spring to early autumn months.\n\n{{climate chart|Scotland 1971-2000<ref name=\"scotland\" />\n|- 0.2|5.0|170.5\n|- 0.1|5.2|123.4\n|0.9|6.9|138.5\n|2.1|9.3|86.2\n|4.5|12.8|79.0\n|7.2|14.9|85.1\n|9.3|16.9|92.1\n|9.2|16.6|107.4\n|7.2|13.9|139.7\n|4.9|10.8|162.6\n|2.0|7.4|165.9\n|0.5|5.7|169.6\n|float=left\n|clear=none\n}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable collapsible\" style=\"width:700px;\"\n! colspan= \"15\" style=\"background: #6688AA; color: #6688AA\" | <span style=\"margin-left: 80px; color: white\"><big>Scotland weather averages</big></span>\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! style=\"background:#dcf0f0; color:navy; height:17px;\"| Month\n! style=\"background:#dcf0f0; color:navy;\"| Jan\n! style=\"background:#dcf0f0; color:navy;\"| Feb\n! style=\"background:#dcf0f0; color:navy;\"| Mar\n! style=\"background:#dcf0f0; color:navy;\"| Apr\n! style=\"background:#dcf0f0; color:navy;\"| May\n! style=\"background:#dcf0f0; color:navy;\"| Jun\n! style=\"background:#dcf0f0; color:navy;\"| Jul\n! style=\"background:#dcf0f0; color:navy;\"| Aug\n! style=\"background:#dcf0f0; color:navy;\"| Sep\n! style=\"background:#dcf0f0; color:navy;\"| Oct\n! style=\"background:#dcf0f0; color:navy;\"| Nov\n! style=\"background:#dcf0f0; color:navy;\"| Dec\n! style=\"background:#dcf0f0; color:navy; border-left: